    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i live in oslo and since its winter and basically dark all day i’ve been feeling super sluggish. i read online that taking a massive dose of vitamin d can help fix that and boost immunity fast. would it be okay to take like 50,000 iu a day for a few weeks just to get my levels way up quickly? feels like a good way to optimize my system for the winter.",
